    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>AIR CHAMBER REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fan clutch from engine and clamp in a vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove socket head capscrews (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200405">Figure 5</hotlnk>) from air chamber (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200405">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1200405" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1200405" filename="../figg12/G1200405.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Disconnecting Air Chamber</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. AIR CHAMBER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SOCKET HEAD CAPSCREW</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Applying air pressure to clutch will aid in removal of air chamber assembly from clutch.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear eye protection when using or applying air pressure.</para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide air chamber assembly off clutch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Examine air chamber for signs of dirt and foreign material. Air chamber should be clean
                    and dry. If not, a condition exists in the vehicle air system and must be corrected before fan
                    clutch is reinstalled.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
